{"tid":1159652,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"澳州樹熊面臨絕種，數目已經降少至無可挽救嘅地步","createTime":"2019-05-18T00:42:02.000Z","updateTime":"2019-05-18T06:34:59.000Z","uid":131691,"like":14,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":24,"replies":[{"pid":"1a6983325678bd9c0806b8b69eeefa42b78fe181","tid":1159652,"uid":131691,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-18T00:42:02.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://news.sky.com/story/koalas-declared-functionally-extinct-across-australia-11721983\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fkoalas-declared-functionally-extinct-across-australia-11721983&d=LRk9npnliL4HefRMP%2BWOkCcuUNiPSPuqsSoNSJcc%2FI4%3D&h=9e9b8d5e\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://news.sky.com/story/koalas-declared-functionally-extinct-across-australia-11721983</a><br />\n<br />\nKoalas are &quot;functionally extinct&quot; in their native Australia, it has been declared.<br />\n<br />\nThe Australian Koala Foundation's chairman Deborah Tabart says there are no more than 80,000 koalas in the country and, while this might seem like a lot, there are not enough breeding adults to support the next generation.<br />\n<br />\nShe said the number was a fraction of the eight million koalas shot for fur and sent to London between 1890 and 1927.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;Functionally extinct&quot; is a scientific term to describe the species as being &quot;beyond the point of recovery&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nRising temperatures and heatwaves causing deforestation have combined with the appetite of various industries and urbanisation to cut down the number of koala habitats.<br />\n<br />\nActivists worry that it would only take a new disease to kill off the remaining koalas."},{"pid":"3d7c61b315b23d1f8b19f80ca35543b776ca1b5d","tid":1159652,"uid":109136,"like":26,"dislike":2,"score":24,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-05-18T00:50:54.000Z","msg":"點算<br />\n佢地咁可愛<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/cry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/norm